      "role": "user",
      "content": "microsoft support is the last place i'd go to report this lol. they're the ones running the protocol. \n\nlook, i'm not talking about standard \"usage telemetry.\" i'm seeing specific sub-routine calls in the kernel logs that seem to sync with specific visual frequencies on the monitor. it's like the OS is trying to find a resonant frequency with the user. it's way too specific to be a \"performance metric.\" if this was just about crashing logs, why would there be modules designed to analyze micro-tremors in input latency that correspond to human ocular refresh cycles? doesnt that seem suspicious to a technical expert like you?",
